  "body": "## üéâ Description\r\n\r\nWhen creating a basic contract, without any functionality whatsoever, that inherits from Crowdsale (i.e. Crowdsale.sol), the aforementioned error occurs. This occurs both on Ganach, Ropsten and Rinkeby. The moment I leave out the inheritance (i.e. \"is Crowdsale\" portion), the contract compiles and migrates just fine to Ganach, Ropsten and Rinkeby.\r\n\r\nWorking code:\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.24;\r\n\r\nimport \"./PrettyToken.sol\";\r\nimport \"../node_modules/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/crowdsale/Crowdsale.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract PrettyTokenSale {\r\n\r\n  constructor(uint256 _rate, address _wallet, ERC20 _token) public {\r\n\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function doNothing() public returns (bool success) {\r\n  \treturn true;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot working code:\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.24;\r\n\r\nimport \"./PrettyToken.sol\";\r\nimport \"../node_modules/openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/crowdsale/Crowdsale.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract PrettyTokenSale is Crowdsale {\r\n\r\n  constructor(uint256 _rate, address _wallet, ERC20 _token) public Crowdsale(_rate, _wallet, _token) {\r\n\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function doNothing() public returns (bool success) {\r\n  \treturn true;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n- [x ] üêõ This is a bug report.\r\n- [ ] üìà This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n<!-- Please check one of the above by placing an x in the box. -->\r\n\r\n## üíª Environment\r\n\r\nNext, we need to know what your environment looks like.\r\n\r\n- Which version of OpenZeppelin are you using?\r\nLatest, on Windows 10. Latest Node. Latest Truffle. Latest everything.\r\n\r\n- What network are you deploying to? Ganache? Ropsten?\r\nGanache, Ropsten, Rinkeby\r\n\r\n- How are you deploying your OpenZeppelin-backed contracts? truffle? Remix? Let us know!\r\n\r\n## üìù Details\r\n\r\nWhen deploying to both Ropsten and Rinkeby, the error I mentioned above happens. When deploying to Ganache I get:\r\n`Error encountered, bailing. Network state unknown. Review successful transactions manually.\r\nError: VM Exception while processing transaction: revert`\r\n\r\n## üî¢ Code To Reproduce Issue [ Good To Have ]\r\n\r\nSee initial report.\r\n\r\n## üëç Other Information\r\nThis also happens when copy-pasting the example Crowdsale contract in the Github. When copy-pasting the actual code from Crowdsale.sol into my own contract, such as to make my contract have the same functionality without inheriting, I get the same error.\r\n",
